# Conclusion

Using `.auto.tfvars` files is a clean and efficient approach for managing automatic environment-specific configurations in Terraform.

The most important takeaway from this activity is:

> Terraform overrides values at the variable level, not at the entire file level.

This behavior provides flexibility and makes Terraform configuration management more predictable and modular in real-world infrastructure deployments.
